 solution to chrts issue.  After risk assessments were performed, and the terminal granting a onetime waiver; we finished loading in Port Arthur without further issues.  \n\n\nFixture Notes:   Lift #3 at the end of the year when we are enjoying almost the top of the market so far at ws169.88 and fairly decent returns which are a little bit doomed by the high bunker costs \n\nVessel\tStena Provence\nVoy#\t2106\nFix#\tJGLobal CVC#3 USG/ Braz\nC/P Date\tJul 21, 2021\nCharterer\tJ Global E\nBroker\tBrazilship\nStart\tRio de Janeiro\nLoad\tTexas City fb Houston\nDischarge\tMaceio fb Santos fb Rio de Janeiro\nCargo\t45,000 mt CPP\nLay/Can\tDec 16-18, 2021 (00:00-16:00)\nRate\tWS 169.88\nComm\tBroker: 1.25%, Agent: 2%\nTCE\nPNL\t$14,400 for 45 days\n($47,800) Bss 15,5 kpd\nDemurrage\t$20,500.00"},{"modifiedDate":"2021-12-23T18:42:02.37","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"New freight rate of 22.79/mt as Port Arthur was included as 2nd load port"},{"modifiedDate":"2021-12-10T18:28:37.78","modifiedByFull":"Fdemosteyrin, Manuel","remark":"Kindly note below preliminary freight assessment for our MT Stena Provence: \n\nTC18 BITR 07/12 \u2013 153,21\nTC18 BITR 08/12 \u2013 174,29\nTC18 BITR 09/12 \u2013 182,14\n\nBss on above we have a minimum rate of WS169,88 please be guided that charterers are still deciding wether vessel calls Rio only or also Santos, therefore we have placed both calculations for perusal:\n\na)\tflat rate for voyage Houston \u002B Tx City \u2013 Maceio \u002B Rio de Janeiro = 20,23 (Attached for perusal)\n\nBss on above = 169,88 X 20,23 X 45.000/100 = 1.546.502,58 USD\n\nb)\tflat rate for voyage Houston \u002B Tx City \u2013 Maceio \u002B Santos \u002B Rio de Janeiro = 22,08 (Attached for perusal)\n\nBss on above = 169,88 X 22,08 X 45.000/100 = 1.689.927,68 USD"}],"offhireList":[],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}